
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-anjum-pana-location-requirements-00.txt'>
    <title>"Requirements for supporting Location-based Authorization Services within the  PANA framework", Farooq Anjum</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-anjum-pana-location-requirements-00.txt</link>
    <description>The PANA protocol provides a means to authenticate clients in an IP network using cryptographic credentials. This document identifies scenarios where there may be a need for a client to provide location credentials, in addition to cryptographic credentials, to gain network access. This document also enumerates the requirements for PANA support of location based services.</description>
    <dc:date>2006-03-03T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
